function clean_column(col::AbstractString)
    return replace(lowercase(strip(col)), r"[\s-]+" => "_")
end
```

This function uses the `lowercase` function to convert all characters in the column name to lowercase. The `strip` function removes any leading or trailing whitespace. Finally, the `replace` function is used with a regular expression to replace any sequence of spaces or hyphens with a single underscore.
